The paper deals with the k-Path problem, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and algorithms. The problem is related to several other problems in computer science, such as k-Tree, r-Dimensional k-Matching, Graph Motif, and Partial Cover. Therefore, the paper is likely to be relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
